Gladys Hulette https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Gladys_Hulette 0 Gladys Hulette (July 21, 1896 – August 8, 1991) was an American silent film actress from Arcade, New York, United States. Her career began in the early years of silent movies and continued until the mid-1930s. She first performed on stage at the age of three and on screen when she was seven years old. Hulette was also a talented artist. Her mother was an opera star. Gladys_Hulette ( July_21_,_1896 – August_8_,_1991 ) was an_American_silent_film_actress from Arcade , New_York , United_States .
